OUTLINE OF THE PROJECT:-
 Embedded systems (Arduino)
 Sensor interfacing
 Control systems (PID)
 Real robotics logic
Project Idea

Build a mobile robot that:-

Moves autonomously
Detects obstacles using sensors
Adjusts its movement using PID control
Avoids collisions smoothly (not jerky)

Components Required:-
Arduino Uno / Nano
Ultrasonic Sensor (HC-SR04)
Motor Driver (L298N)
2 DC Motors + Wheels
Chassis
Battery pack
Jumper wires

System Architecture:-

Sensors → Arduino → Control Logic → Motor Driver → Motors

Ultrasonic → distance
Arduino → decision making
PID → smooth turning
Motors → movement

Core Logic
Step 1: Read distance
Ultrasonic sensor measures distance continuously
Step 2: Decision making
If obstacle < threshold → turn
Else → move forward
Step 3: Apply PID control
Instead of sudden turns, use PID for smooth control


